        "discriminators": [
          "A SPLAT, not a splash. Viscosity means the liquid does not atomise: there is no bright spray tail, so high_band_energy collapses and the spectral_centroid_hz lands around 1 kHz — roughly a third of WATER-SPLASH's ~2.6 kHz. Dull, dark, damped, over fast.",
          "Against WATER-SPLASH and WATER-IMPACT: identical morphology (a single sharp transient), completely different timbre. The high_band_energy / spectral_centroid_hz pair is the whole discrimination, and it is a real one.",
          "Against LIQUID & MUD-SUCTION: a splat is a hard onset with an immediate decay; a suck is a sustained, pitch-gliding pull.",
          "Squelch and squish sit on the boundary with MOVEMENT: if the contact is sustained rather than percussive, prefer MOVEMENT."
        ],
        "confusable_with": [
          "WATRSplsh",
          "WATRImpt",
          "LIQMvmt",
          "LIQSuct",
          "GORESplt"
