        "discriminators": [
          "Oozing and glooping: a continuous, LOW, damped bed. Viscosity suppresses the high-frequency turbulence that gives water its brightness, so the centroid sits near 1 kHz against WATER-MOVEMENT's ~2 kHz, and high_band_energy is a third of it.",
          "Against WATER-MOVEMENT and WATER-FLOW: same morphology, dark timbre. The spectral_slope_db_per_octave (~-10.5) is far steeper than any water flow.",
          "Against LIQUID & MUD-BUBBLES: MOVEMENT is a bed with occasional pitched gloops; BUBBLES is dominated by them (higher harmonicity, resolvable rising chirps).",
          "Against LIQUID & MUD-IMPACT: continuous, not a discrete splat."
