        "discriminators": [
          "A suck is a GLIDE, and that is what makes it detectable. As a plunger or a slurp closes the cavity, the trapped-air resonance sweeps upward: positive pitch_slope_semitones_per_second and positive spectral_centroid_slope_hz_per_second, over a few hundred ms. No other LIQUID & MUD subcategory has a monotonic trajectory.",
          "Also unusually pitched for this category (harmonicity ~0.42) — a resonating air cavity, not broadband liquid noise.",
          "Against LIQUID & MUD-IMPACT: a splat is front-loaded (low envelope_temporal_centroid, immediate decay); a suck is BACK-loaded (envelope_temporal_centroid ~0.55) and builds. Envelope shape alone separates them.",
          "Against LIQUID & MUD-MOVEMENT: MOVEMENT is a stationary bed with no directed trajectory.",
          "Against WATER-DRAIN: a drain gurgles and sucks too, but continuously and without the single clean upward sweep; a drain is also thin and bright where this is thick and low."
